ative and invisible to screen readers. The text label must convey the status on its own — never rely on the dot alone to communicate meaning."],[329,"The component accepts standard `className` and `style` props:"],[338,"The component also includes accessibility attributes:"],[331,"The component automatically adds data attributes for styling hooks:"],[306,"The component extends `BentoIconProps` and passes through all standard HTML attributes and accessibility props to the underlying Bento Icon component. This includes:"],[1223,"The component sets ARIA attributes on interactive and structural elements as needed."],[1129,"The component uses `container-type: inline-size` and fills its parent width. Ensure the parent has a defined width:"],[1069,"The component uses VisX primitives for optimal SVG rendering:"],[92,"The controlled carousel is a carousel that is controlled by the `activeIndex` prop."],[74,"The critical button signifies to the user a destructive action will take place."],[195,"The decorative SVG and output text are hidden via `aria-hidden=\"true\"`"],[91,"The default carousel is a carousel that is uncontrolled, it shows the first slide by default. You can also pass the `defaultActiveIndex` prop to the `Carousel` component to set the initial active slide index."],[502,"The default modal exposes a `title`, `description`, and `children` content area. Open and close state is managed automatically by `ModalTrigger`."],[570,"The default pagination is uncontrolled. It renders prev/next buttons and one dot per page. The `total` prop sets the number of items."],[71,"The default/tertiary button is the base for all other buttons in the system. It provides no significant visual treatment other than to provide indication for the user to take a common action."],[48,"The dismiss button defaults to `aria-label=\"Close\"`. Override it via `ariaLabels={{ close: '...' }}` to provide more specific context for screen readers (e.g. `\"Dismiss payment warning\"`). This is especial